b4.ezboard.com/umacathenecro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maca the Necro</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>w4nn4b3!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>1/20/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>5:30:39 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Quest: Frozen Orb *Spoiler*</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Okay.. Maca's first guide. Bare with me.<br>
<br>
This miniature quest takes place in the <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/maps.asp?Action=Description&Id=109">Eastern Wastes</a> zone near the orc fort and coldain outpost, at about n3000, 0. <br>
<br>
Garadain Glacierbane wants you to return to his lookout the Ry'gorr Invasion plans held within the Ry'gorr Messenger's grasp. The messenger is green to a level 49 and is quite easy, at that. He is a one hour spawn and spawns at or near n3100, n400, on a hill north of the tree, which is north of the opening of the ry'gorr fort. He always drops the plans.<br>
<br>
Before you continue, be SURE you are a 49+ necro or 40+ with a full, balanced group. When you turn in the Invasion Plans to the coldain lookout, Scarbrow Hy'gukk and 8 (yes, count them-- 8) Ry'gorr Oracles will spawn near the two trees west-southwest from the Coldain camp. Scarbrow himself is a level 47 shadowknight (blue con to 49 nec) and the oracles are low 40's.<br>
<br>
*HOWEVER*<br>
<br>
There is a way to spawn Scarbrow without the mean Oracles to spawn. Have a friend stand between the two trees where Scarbrow spawns, at the *EXACT* location of n2689, n50, while invisible. *PETS DO NOT WORK!!*<br>
<br>
Now for the strategy. Put up Diamondskin, Arch shielding, Summon your pet, augment him, and med up. Load up the following spells: 49 lifetap, Bond of death, *ENGULFING* darkness, Invoke fear, Harmshield, Ignite bones, Feign Death. Fill the final spot with whatever you want, I used venom of the snake for the extra damage. Once you have FM, have your friend get to the location and invis himself. Now, here comes the battle. Turn in the invasion plans. The lookout will tell you that the orcs are coming-- if your friend did it right, only Scarbrow will spawn. If not, forget about it, you can't do it (unless if you have a 50+ enchanter). Note: If *Anything* goes wrong, Feign Death and /q out to get off of Scarbrow's agro list-- he triple hits for 130's, and Invasion Plans are not hard to come by =)<br>
<br>
Now, Scarbrow will shout some nonsense. Quickly run past the Coldain camp and send your pet in to take the harm touch. Immediatly fear him and then snare him. I feared first because if he resists snare then you're pretty much dead.. he doesn't care much for fighting pets. Remember, if anything goes wrong, immediatly feign death. If the first fear was not resisted, he should head past the Coldain camp. Blammo, you get some free help. Start alternating Ignite Bones and Drain Soul-- inflict as much damage as possible so that those damn smurfs wont take the kill. Re-fear when necessary. By now you should have one dead orc.<br>
<br>
9 out of 10 times you should get the kill. If that is the case then congratulate yourself on a job well done (or in my case, start breathing again).<br>
<br>
I am saddened to say that Verant has recently *nerfed* Scarbrow's loot. On every corpse you should get Scarbrow's Head as loot. This head is used for the fifth Coldain Ring quest (turn in the head with the Platinum Coldain Insignia Ring and the head to earn the Obsidian Coldain Insignia Ring). You should also get *either* a ry'gorr scalp, a Velium two handed sword, the coveted Frozen Orb, or some other trash.<br>
<br>
The Frozen Orb is MAGIC LORE +3 wis +3 int +40 mana +2 ac range slot only, NEC WIZ MAG ENC DRU CLR SHM. I have killed Scarbrow about 8 times and he has only dropped the Frozen Orb the first time (I'm lucky like that).. Hopefully your luck will be better.<br>
<br>
If you try to take down Scarbrow, I wish you the best of luck in getting your frozen orb =)<br>
<br>
If you have any questions, feel free to email me =).<br>
